data.chText: 荷兰的；荷兰人的；荷兰语的
data.enText: of or connected with the Netherlands, its people or its language

data.chText: （同某人）各付各的账，平摊费用
data.enText: to share the cost of sth with sb

value.def: Dutch means belonging or relating to the Netherlands, or to its people, language, or culture.
value.tran: 荷兰的;荷兰语的;荷兰人的

value.def: The Dutch are the people of the Netherlands.

example.ex: The Dutch developed a custom by which children put out shoes which Saint Nicholas would fill with gifts when he came visiting.
example.tran: 荷兰人有一套自己的风俗，孩子们会将鞋子放在外面，圣诞老人到来时便会在里面装满礼品。

value.def: Dutch is the language that is spoken by the people who live in the Netherlands.
If two or more people go Dutch, each of them pays their own bill, for example in a restaurant.

example.ex: We went Dutch on a meal in the new restaurant in Shaftesbury Avenue.
example.tran: 我们在沙夫茨伯里大道一家新开的饭馆里AA制吃的饭。

value.tran: 各付各的账;平摊费用;AA 制

trans: 荷兰式拍卖(把价格逐步降低到有人愿买为止)
